lass_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Base Pipeline Class. Contains basic pipelines methods like *fit*, *transform*, *fit_transfrom*, *save_pipeline* and *load_pipeline*. Used in building different pipelines\n    "]}, {"name": "price_pred.pipelines.ETLPipeline", "bases": ["BasePipeline"], "methods": [{"name": "price_pred.pipelines.ETLPipeline.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "merge_list", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "unique_features", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "feature_map", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "outliers_map", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.pipelines.ETLPipeline._create_pipeline", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Creates the ETL pipeline with the specified transformers."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Pipeline according to ETL scheme\n\nPreprocessing Steps:\n1. **UniquenessTransformer** : Deletes simmilar records from dataframe \n2. **MergeTransformer**: As the data we work with is separated into few files, in this step we merge all data together\n3. **NegativeValueTransformer** : Deletes records with negative price_values\n4. **OutliersCleaningTransformer** : Deletes detected outliers\n5. **DtypesTransformer** : Assign corresponding data types for features\n\nAll Transformers in this steps are defined in `price_pred.transformers` module"]}, {"name": "price_pred.pipelines.EDAPipeline", "bases": ["BasePipeline"], "methods": [{"name": "price_pred.pipelines.EDAPipeline.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "outliers_map", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "date_column", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "price_columns", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "n_clusters", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "columns_target_encoding", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "new_product_delta", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.pipelines.EDAPipeline._create_pipeline", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Creates the EDA pipeline with the specified transformers."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Pipeline according to EDA scheme\n\nPreprocessing Steps:\n1. **OutliersCleaningTransformer**: Deletes Outliers according to outliers map\n2. **LagsEncoder**: Create Lags for price and sales features\n3. **SeasonalityTransformer**: Creates new features based on dates \n4. **EventsTransformer**: Creates features, which correspond to different events \n5. **PriceClusterTransform**: Create features for price clusters separation\n6. **NewCategoriesTransformer**: Create features based on item categories and shops\n7. **CategoryTargetEncoder**: Encodes categorical features using **TargetEncoding**\n8. **NewProductsTransformer**: Deletes first sales of items as they usually higher for brand new items\n\nAll Transformers in this steps are defined in `price_pred.transformers` module"]}, {"name": "price_pred.pipelines.AgregationPipeline", "bases": ["BasePipeline"], "methods": [{"name": "price_pred.pipelines.AgregationPipeline.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "start_date", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "periods", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.pipelines.AgregationPipeline._create_pipeline", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Creates the Aggregation pipeline with the specified transformers."]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Pipeline for data aggregation.\n\nPreprocessing Steps:\n1. **AggregationTransformer**: Aggregates sales data by month\n\nAll Transformers in this steps are defined in `price_pred.transformers` module"]}, {"name": "price_pred.pipelines.TestPreprocessingPipeline", "bases": ["BasePipeline"], "methods": [{"name": "price_pred.pipelines.TestPreprocessingPipeline.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "raw_train", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "agg_train", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "etl_eda_pipeline", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "start_date", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "period", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "features", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.pipelines.TestPreprocessingPipeline._create_pipeline", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Pipeline for test data preprocessing\n\nPreprocessing Steps:\n1. **TestPreprocessTransformer**: Transforms Test Data to the shape which corresponds to original Train Data\n2. **TestTrainMergeTransformer**: Concatenates Test and Train Datasets\n3. **Feature Extraction**: Extracts new features using a bit modified ETL-EDA pipeline.\n4. **FeatureSelectionTransformer**: Selects best features. **This implementation does not find them, but just chooses from list defined by user.** If you want to find them, use `price_pred.feature_selection.VotingSelector` \n5. **TestSetExtractionTransformer**. As we've merged train and test set, in this step, we delete train set and save only preprocessed test data.\n\nAll Transformers in this steps (except of **Feature Extraction** step) are defined in `price_pred.transformers` module"]}, {"name": "price_pred.pipelines.TrainPreprocessingPipeline", "bases": ["BasePipeline"], "methods": [{"name": "price_pred.pipelines.TrainPreprocessingPipeline.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "merge_list", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "unique_features", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "feature_map", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "start_date", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "periods", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "outliers", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.pipelines.TrainPreprocessingPipeline._create_pipeline", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Pipeline for train Preprocessing\n\nPreprocessing Steps:\n1. **ETLPipeline**: Transforms DataFrame according to ETL scheme. Look `price_pred.pipelines.ETLPipeline` for more details.\n2. **AggregationTransformer** : Aggregates data by months\n\nAll Transformers in this steps (except of `ETLPipeline`) are defined in `price_pred.transformers` module"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "price_pred", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "price_pred.feature_selection", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "price_pred.feature_selection.VoitingSelector", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "price_pred.feature_selection.VoitingSelector.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.feature_selection.VoitingSelector._select_pearson", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "X", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.feature_selection.VoitingSelector._select_mi", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "X", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.feature_selection.VoitingSelector._select_vif", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "X", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.feature_selection.VoitingSelector._select_anova", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "X", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.feature_selection.VoitingSelector.select", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "X", "type": {"name": "pd.DataFrame", "xref": {"fqname": "pandas.DataFrame", "project": "pandas"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type": {"name": "pd.Series | np.ndarray", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "voting_threshold", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "pd.DataFrame", "xref": {"fqname": "pandas.DataFrame", "project": "pandas"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["_summary_\n\nArgs:\n    X (pd.DataFrame): Source DataFrame, in which we are looking for best features to choose\n    y (pd.Series | np.ndarray): Corresponding target values for X\n    voting_threshold (float, optional): Defines a percents of votes, needed for feature to be selected_. Defaults to 0.5.\n\nReturns:\n    pd.DataFrame: DataFrame with best features_"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Class for feature selection step.\n\n**VotingSelector** use 4 methods for feature selection:\n\n- Pearson Correlation\n- Mutual Information\n- Variance-Inflation Factor (VIF)\n- Analysis of variance (Anova)\n\nEach of this methods vote for best features according to their methods and statistics.\nFinal subset of best fetures is defined by *voting_threshhold* parameter,\nwhich corresponds to percent of votes for feature to be added to best feature subset"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "price_pred.transformers", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "price_pred.transformers.get_city_name", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.transformers.get_shop_type", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.transformers.get_group", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "price_pred.transformers.TrainTransformer", "bases": ["BaseEstimator", "TransformerMixin"], "methods": [{"name": "price_pred.transformers.TrainTransformer.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "test", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "price_pred.transformers.TrainTransformer.fit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "X", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type":